description:
SfpModule: Table containing SFP module attributes for various cells, including timestamps, location, identifiers, data type, format version, and administrative state.
dateTime: Timestamp of the data record.
Area_Name: Name of the geographical area.
CellId: Unique identifier of the cell site.
Id2: Redundant cell identifier (likely a duplicate of CellId).
Id3:  Additional identifier potentially related to equipment or location.
Id4:  Another identifier, possibly related to data type or source.
vsDataType: Specifies the type of data as SFP module data.
vsDataFormatVersion: Version of the data format used (Ericsson-specific).
SfpModule.sfpModuleId: Unique identifier of the SFP module.
SfpModule.administrativeState: Administrative state of the SFP module (e.g., LOCKED/UNLOCKED).
queries: Find all SFP modules with administrativeState = LOCKED in Area_Name = "Downtown".
Show me the dateTime and sfpModuleId for all SFP modules where vsDataFormatVersion = "2.0" and CellId = "ABC123XYZ".
What is the count of distinct sfpModuleId values for Area_Name = "Suburbia"  between 2023-10-26 00:00:00 and 2023-10-27 00:00:00?
Retrieve all SfpModule records where Id3 LIKE "%router%" and administrativeState = "UNLOCKED".
List all sfpModuleId, CellId, and Area_Name for SFP modules with vsDataType = "SFP module data" and a dateTime within the last 24 hours.
